<paragraph blockId="10.[159,1116,1293,1732]" pageId="10" pageNumber="1903">
<emphasis box="[199,334,1389,1413]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1903">Description.</emphasis>
Carapace smooth; rostrum very short, broad, distally rounded, reaching level of antero-lateral margin of carapace (
<figureCitation box="[774,881,1421,1445]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="11.[154,170,1155,1177]" captionTargetBox="[160,1111,178,1110]" captionTargetId="figure-124@11.[154,1112,170,1117]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIG. 5. Bermudacaris australiensis sp. nov. Holotype, ovigerous female (CL 2.7 mm; NTM- Cr 000476). (A) Anterior part of carapace and cephalic appendages, dorsal view; (B) same, lateral view; (C) carapace and eye, lateral view; (D) right antennule, lateral view; (E) left uropod, dorsal view. Scales: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4658717" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4658717/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="1903">figure 5A</figureCitation>
); rostral carina and orbital teeth absent; orbital concavity very shallow; antero-lateral margin continuous with ventro-lateral margin without formation of pterygostomian angle; cardiac notch conspicuous (
<figureCitation box="[494,600,1517,1541]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="11.[154,170,1155,1177]" captionTargetBox="[160,1111,178,1110]" captionTargetId="figure-124@11.[154,1112,170,1117]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIG. 5. Bermudacaris australiensis sp. nov. Holotype, ovigerous female (CL 2.7 mm; NTM- Cr 000476). (A) Anterior part of carapace and cephalic appendages, dorsal view; (B) same, lateral view; (C) carapace and eye, lateral view; (D) right antennule, lateral view; (E) left uropod, dorsal view. Scales: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4658717" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4658717/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="1903">figure 5C</figureCitation>
). Eye-stalks exposed dorsally and laterally (
<figureCitation box="[167,314,1549,1573]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="11.[154,170,1155,1177]" captionTargetBox="[160,1111,178,1110]" captionTargetId="figure-124@11.[154,1112,170,1117]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIG. 5. Bermudacaris australiensis sp. nov. Holotype, ovigerous female (CL 2.7 mm; NTM- Cr 000476). (A) Anterior part of carapace and cephalic appendages, dorsal view; (B) same, lateral view; (C) carapace and eye, lateral view; (D) right antennule, lateral view; (E) left uropod, dorsal view. Scales: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4658717" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4658717/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="1903">figure 5A, B</figureCitation>
), mesial margins not parallel and separated from each other by median space; cornea well pigmented, occupying most of distal third of eye-stalk (
<figureCitation box="[167,274,1613,1637]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="11.[154,170,1155,1177]" captionTargetBox="[160,1111,178,1110]" captionTargetId="figure-124@11.[154,1112,170,1117]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIG. 5. Bermudacaris australiensis sp. nov. Holotype, ovigerous female (CL 2.7 mm; NTM- Cr 000476). (A) Anterior part of carapace and cephalic appendages, dorsal view; (B) same, lateral view; (C) carapace and eye, lateral view; (D) right antennule, lateral view; (E) left uropod, dorsal view. Scales: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4658717" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4658717/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="1903">figure 5A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[159,1116,1293,1732]" lastBlockId="11.[154,1111,1324,1518]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="1904" pageId="10" pageNumber="1903">
Antennular peduncle with second segment as long as visible portion of first segment; stylocerite short, not appressed, not reaching distal margin of first segment, tip acute (
<figureCitation box="[424,531,1708,1732]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="11.[154,170,1155,1177]" captionTargetBox="[160,1111,178,1110]" captionTargetId="figure-124@11.[154,1112,170,1117]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIG. 5. Bermudacaris australiensis sp. nov. Holotype, ovigerous female (CL 2.7 mm; NTM- Cr 000476). (A) Anterior part of carapace and cephalic appendages, dorsal view; (B) same, lateral view; (C) carapace and eye, lateral view; (D) right antennule, lateral view; (E) left uropod, dorsal view. Scales: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4658717" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4658717/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="1903">figure 5A</figureCitation>
); ventro-mesial carina on first segment low, terminating anteriorly in acute tooth (
<figureCitation box="[608,716,1324,1348]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="11.[154,170,1155,1177]" captionTargetBox="[160,1111,178,1110]" captionTargetId="figure-124@11.[154,1112,170,1117]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIG. 5. Bermudacaris australiensis sp. nov. Holotype, ovigerous female (CL 2.7 mm; NTM- Cr 000476). (A) Anterior part of carapace and cephalic appendages, dorsal view; (B) same, lateral view; (C) carapace and eye, lateral view; (D) right antennule, lateral view; (E) left uropod, dorsal view. Scales: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4658717" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4658717/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="1904">figure 5D</figureCitation>
); outer flagellum not subdivided. Antenna with basicerite bearing ventro-lateral tooth; carpocerite slender, twice as long as scaphocerite and exceeding distal margin of antennular peduncle (
<figureCitation box="[993,1097,1392,1416]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="11.[154,170,1155,1177]" captionTargetBox="[160,1111,178,1110]" captionTargetId="figure-124@11.[154,1112,170,1117]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIG. 5. Bermudacaris australiensis sp. nov. Holotype, ovigerous female (CL 2.7 mm; NTM- Cr 000476). (A) Anterior part of carapace and cephalic appendages, dorsal view; (B) same, lateral view; (C) carapace and eye, lateral view; (D) right antennule, lateral view; (E) left uropod, dorsal view. Scales: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4658717" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4658717/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="1904">figure 5B</figureCitation>
); scaphocerite rectangular-oval in general outline, with nearly straight lateral margin, nearly reaching distal margin of second segment of antennular peduncle, with strong disto-lateral tooth slightly over-reaching distal margin of rounded blade
</paragraph>
