<paragraph blockId="11.[154,1111,1529,1584]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1904">
(
<figureCitation box="[161,270,1529,1553]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="11.[154,170,1155,1177]" captionTargetBox="[160,1111,178,1110]" captionTargetId="figure-124@11.[154,1112,170,1117]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIG. 5. Bermudacaris australiensis sp. nov. Holotype, ovigerous female (CL 2.7 mm; NTM- Cr 000476). (A) Anterior part of carapace and cephalic appendages, dorsal view; (B) same, lateral view; (C) carapace and eye, lateral view; (D) right antennule, lateral view; (E) left uropod, dorsal view. Scales: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4658717" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4658717/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="1904">figure 5A</figureCitation>
). Mouthparts typical for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rafinesque" authorityYear="1815" box="[463,578,1560,1584]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="1904" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Alpheidae</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[593,678,1560,1584]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="12.[159,175,1369,1391]" captionTargetBox="[9,1115,172,1329]" captionTargetId="figure-33@12.[159,1117,170,1331]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIG. 6. Bermudacaris australiensis sp. nov. Holotype, ovigerous female (CL 2.7 mm; NTM- Cr 000476). Right appendages. (A) Mandible, mesio-ventral view; (B) maxillule, ventral view; (C) maxilla, ventral view; (D) first maxilliped, ventral view; (E) second maxilliped, ventral view; inset, epipod and podobranch, dorsal view; (F) third maxilliped, lateral view; (G) basal part of third maxilliped, showing epipod, coxal lateral process and arthrobranch, ventro-lateral view; (H) same, dorsal view; (I) third pereopod, lateral. Scales: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4658721" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4658721/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="1904">figure 6</figureCitation>
A–E). Second maxilliped with bilobed
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[154,1111,1595,1721]" lastBlockId="12.[159,1116,1603,1727]" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="1905" pageId="11" pageNumber="1904">
podobranch (
<figureCitation box="[307,413,1595,1619]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="12.[159,175,1369,1391]" captionTargetBox="[9,1115,172,1329]" captionTargetId="figure-33@12.[159,1117,170,1331]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIG. 6. Bermudacaris australiensis sp. nov. Holotype, ovigerous female (CL 2.7 mm; NTM- Cr 000476). Right appendages. (A) Mandible, mesio-ventral view; (B) maxillule, ventral view; (C) maxilla, ventral view; (D) first maxilliped, ventral view; (E) second maxilliped, ventral view; inset, epipod and podobranch, dorsal view; (F) third maxilliped, lateral view; (G) basal part of third maxilliped, showing epipod, coxal lateral process and arthrobranch, ventro-lateral view; (H) same, dorsal view; (I) third pereopod, lateral. Scales: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4658721" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4658721/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="1904">figure 6E</figureCitation>
). Third maxilliped (
<figureCitation box="[638,740,1595,1619]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="12.[159,175,1369,1391]" captionTargetBox="[9,1115,172,1329]" captionTargetId="figure-33@12.[159,1117,170,1331]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIG. 6. Bermudacaris australiensis sp. nov. Holotype, ovigerous female (CL 2.7 mm; NTM- Cr 000476). Right appendages. (A) Mandible, mesio-ventral view; (B) maxillule, ventral view; (C) maxilla, ventral view; (D) first maxilliped, ventral view; (E) second maxilliped, ventral view; inset, epipod and podobranch, dorsal view; (F) third maxilliped, lateral view; (G) basal part of third maxilliped, showing epipod, coxal lateral process and arthrobranch, ventro-lateral view; (H) same, dorsal view; (I) third pereopod, lateral. Scales: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4658721" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4658721/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="1904">figure 6F</figureCitation>
) elongated, reaching far beyond distal end of antennal peduncle; antepenultimate segment robust; ultimate segment armed with strong spines on distal half of superior margin; lateral plate on coxa conspicuous, rounded oval in shape (
<figureCitation box="[606,757,1697,1721]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="12.[159,175,1369,1391]" captionTargetBox="[9,1115,172,1329]" captionTargetId="figure-33@12.[159,1117,170,1331]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIG. 6. Bermudacaris australiensis sp. nov. Holotype, ovigerous female (CL 2.7 mm; NTM- Cr 000476). Right appendages. (A) Mandible, mesio-ventral view; (B) maxillule, ventral view; (C) maxilla, ventral view; (D) first maxilliped, ventral view; (E) second maxilliped, ventral view; inset, epipod and podobranch, dorsal view; (F) third maxilliped, lateral view; (G) basal part of third maxilliped, showing epipod, coxal lateral process and arthrobranch, ventro-lateral view; (H) same, dorsal view; (I) third pereopod, lateral. Scales: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4658721" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4658721/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="1904">figure 6G, H</figureCitation>
); exopod short, not reaching distal third of antepenultimate segment; strap-like epipod and single arthrobranch present.
</paragraph>
